<br>
His eyes took in everything, every moment, every preparation.  He saw a vertically challenged amazon trying to throw a rope over the end of a rather tall pole and having quite the difficult time with it.  He stood and approached her casually, &quot;May I assist you with that?&quot;  He flashed her a soft smile only to have her turn and virtually hiss at him, &quot;I can do it myself, I don't need a man whore's assistance.&quot;  Theseus blinked, taken aback by her statement.  He started to open his mouth to explain himself, but was greeted with a dagger, and another growl, &quot;I said, I don't need no man's assistance.&quot;  He nodded, &quot;Very well then.  I'll just be right over there if you decide to use the tool given you this day.&quot;  He smirked lightly and resumed his seat to watch with amusement now as she struggled to secure the rope. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alkariawolf@amazonsunite>AlkariaWolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#993300>(5/1/03 9:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Cold River </span><hr size=1> Alkaria had left her mother's side to get ready for the celebration. As her mother had went to get ready, she slipped down to the river, following the young prince. She knew that if she were caught, she would be punished for sure. But for some odd reason, Alkaria was intrigued by this young prince. She watched carefully and sliently in the shadows of the trees near the river, watching him bath and dress. <br>
She also watched him leave and head towards the celebration. As she ran to get ready, Alkaria noticed that her mother was leaveing the hut and heading towards Del's hut. <br>
 &quot;I have to hurry. Mom will know that I have been up to something.&quot; She said to herself as she ran into the hut and quickly got ready. <br>
<br>
 After finding her green cloak, she placed her finest leathers on and fastened her cloak onto her back, then out the door she ran. The celebration was already underway when Alkaria arrived. She looked around for the prince, not seeing him directly, she went over and got herself something to drink.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#993300>(5/1/03 12:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Cold River </span><hr size=1> Alysia was a Scynthian, but she gave honor to her Sister Goddesses, for they were the Mother's of her sister tribes.<br>
She stood in her hut trying her best to wrap her new green cloths. <br>
<br>
&quot;Flipping cloths must have shrunk.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yeah, keep thinking that Aly. She continued to reach around her weight gaining stomach and eventually tied the strings behind her back.<br>
She sighed and looked in the mirror as she wrapped a small green leather string into the braid of her hair. <br>
She then looked down to Scythe, who had accompanied her to Themiscrya.<br>
<br>
The two walked out into the village, and awaited the rest of their athelfi. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
